value.title: Mike Pence to join Heritage Foundation to 'lead the conservative movement into the future'
value.excerpt: Former Vice President Mike Pence is joining a think tank, the first official step on how he plans to stay active in public and political life.

value.title: Psaki defends Biden's 'vast majority' are 'decent' comments about FBI agents
value.excerpt: The White House doubled down on President Biden’s remarks Tuesday saying that a “vast majority” of law enforcement officers were “decent, honorable people” after two FBI agents were killed in the line of duty.

value.title: Psaki's resurfaced tweets slam Trump, Sanders supporters, severely undercutting 'unity' message
value.excerpt: President Biden often invoked a message of national unity on the 2020 campaign trail and since taking office last month – but did his top spokesperson get the message?

value.title: Iranian resistance leader says regime 'at its weakest point,' urges Biden to hold it to account
value.excerpt: EXCLUSIVE: The leader of the main Iranian resistance group tells Fox News that the regime in Tehran is at its "weakest point" in its history, and is calling on the Biden administration to hold the regime accountable for its human rights violations.

value.title: Mitt Romney Points Out GOP Wasn't Concerned About Debt, 'Spending Massively' Under Trump
value.excerpt: The Utah Republican highlighted that under GOP leadership the U.S. was "adding almost a trillion dollars a year to the national debt."

value.title: Biden, Harris pay respects to Capitol officer killed in riot
value.excerpt: Vice President Kamala Harris and her husband, Doug Emhoff, have paid their respects to slain Capitol Police Officer Brian Sicknick as he lay in honor in the U.S. Capitol

value.title: Washington Post: Manhattan DA considering prosecuting Steve Bannon after Trump pardon
value.excerpt: The Manhattan District Attorney's Office is considering bringing state charges against Steve Bannon related to the same border wall fundraising campaign fraud scheme for which he was federally charged and then granted a presidential pardon, according to The Washington Post.

value.title: Biden says ‘no one in our family’ will be involved in government decisions
value.excerpt: President Biden said he intends to keep his family and his administration separate as reports surrounding the business dealings of his son and brother raised questions of potential impropriety.

value.title: Trump powers GOP schism over Taylor Greene and Cheney
value.excerpt: The Republican civil war hits a critical moment on Wednesday over the fate of two prominent lawmakers who represent rival visions for a party torn by the toxic but still powerful influence of Donald Trump.

value.title: U.S. will not expel unaccompanied migrant children under Trump-era policy now being reviewed
value.excerpt: President Biden ordered his administration to review a CDC order that allows U.S. border officials to swiftly expel migrants without a court hearing.

value.title: Biden: No family members will be involved in any government decisions
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden vowed that no one in his extended family will have sway over government decisions in an interview with People magazine published Wednesday.

value.title: Biden shows flexibility but tells House to ‘go big’ on aid
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden is telling House Democrats he’s not married to all the specifics of the $1.9 trillion COVID rescue plan

value.title: Trade to be part of Biden's China strategy, not driving force: ex-USTR official
value.excerpt: Trade will be a part of President Joe Biden's overall negotiation policy with China, but it won't be the driving force in Sino-U.S. relations, as it was under former President Donald Trump, a former official at the Office of the U.

value.title: Bidens pay their respects to Capitol Police Officer Brian Sicknick as officer lies in honor at Capitol
value.excerpt: The body of the late US Capitol Police Officer Brian D. Sicknick arrived Tuesday night to lie in honor in the US Capitol Rotunda, less than four weeks since he died after responding to the violent riot that erupted in the building.

value.title: Georgia secretary of state investigating whether pro-Trump attorney voted illegally
value.excerpt: Georgia Secretary of State Brad Raffensperger has launched an investigation into whether attorney Lin Wood voted as a legal resident in the November election, a source with Raffensperger's office confirmed to CNN.

value.title: Sen. Kennedy blasts 'immeasurably foolish' Biden orders that will 'gut Louisiana like a fish'
value.excerpt: Sen. John Kennedy, R-La., warned Tuesday that President Biden's sweeping executive orders related to the industrial energy sector and immigration will be detrimental to both the nation and, in the former case, his home state.

value.title: Chicago Mayor Lori Lightfoot blames Trump for standoff between city’s public schools and teachers union
value.excerpt: Chicago Mayor Lori Lightfoot on Tuesday blamed the impasse between the city’s public schools and teachers union on President Donald Trump for not being able to roll out a nationwide vaccine program while he was in office.

value.title: Jan. 6 rally organizer planning 'MAGA Sellout' tour targeting Republicans who 'betrayed' Trump
value.excerpt: Pro-Trump organizers are planning a cross-country recruiting effort to attract primary challengers targeting Republicans who they say "betrayed" former President Trump.

value.title: Dems: Trump aimed 'loaded cannon' of supporters at Capitol
value.excerpt: Donald Trump endangered the lives of all members of Congress when he aimed a mob of supporters “like a loaded cannon” at the U.S. Capitol, House Democrats said Tuesday in making their most detailed case yet for why the former president should be convicted and permanently barred from office.

value.title: Sen. Kaine sets aside Trump censure resolution: 'There's not enough support on either side'
value.excerpt: Sens. Tim Kaine and Susan Collins have set aside the bipartisan effort to censure former President Trump for his role in the Jan. 6 Capitol riot for lack of support from both Democrats and Republicans.

value.title: Graham urges acting AG to 'refrain from interfering' in Durham, Hunter Biden probes amid Garland confirmation
value.excerpt: Sen. value.title: Trump Previews Impeachment Defense: It Wasn’t Incitement, It Was Free Speech
value.excerpt: Donald Trump’s lawyers on Tuesday previewed their defense of the ex-president during next week’s impeachment trial, responding to pre-trial brief filed by House managers accusing him of a “grievous betrayal” of his oath of office for inciting last month’s attack on the Capitol.

value.title: Whistleblower accuses former Trump official of 'abuse of authority' for last day deal with ICE union
value.excerpt: Former senior Department of Homeland Security official Ken Cuccinelli is accused in a new whistleblower complaint of mismanagement, waste and abuse of authority over a deal he signed with a union representing Immigration and Customs Enforcement officers that endorsed President Donald Trump.

value.title: Trump pollster says Covid-19, not voter fraud, to blame for reelection loss
value.excerpt: Former President Donald Trump lost reelection over voters' dissatisfaction with his handling of the Covid-19 pandemic, his own pollster said in a post-campaign report, disputing the key argument Trump has repeatedly made that he lost because of voter fraud, despite a lack of evidence.
